    <section class="section" id="projects">
        <h3>Projects</h3>

        <div class="interactive-slot">
            <h4>Data Generator Project (MSU Burgess Institute of Science)</h4>
            <p>For this project, I built a simple yet effective data generator to create mock datasets for testing and analysis. This was particularly useful for simulating real-world data before working with actual company datasets.</p>
            <p>The script randomly generates names, ages, and scores, making it great for testing database operations and visualizations.</p>
            <img src="URL_TO_YOUR_DATA_GENERATOR_IMAGE" alt="Data Generator Screenshot" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 10px;">
            <pre>
import random
import pandas as pd

names = ["Stephen", "Mark", "Ben", "Abby", "Emma"]
data = [{"Name": random.choice(names), "Age": random.randint(18, 40), "Score": random.randint(50, 100)} for _ in range(10)]

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)
            </pre>
            <p>This script helped me learn how to generate structured data efficiently. I used Python’s random module and Pandas to store the generated values in a structured format, making it easy to analyze and manipulate later.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="interactive-slot">
            <h4>Data Visualization Project</h4>
            <p>I created this project to explore how visual representations can help interpret data more effectively. Using Matplotlib, I built a simple bar chart that visualizes randomly generated scores.</p>
            <img src="URL_TO_YOUR_DATA_VISUALIZATION_IMAGE" alt="Data Visualization Screenshot" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 10px;">
            <pre>
import random
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

names = ["David", "Antonio", "Nolan", "Ashton", "Bethany"]
scores = [random.randint(50, 100) for _ in names]

plt.bar(names, scores, color='green')
plt.xlabel("Names")
plt.ylabel("Scores")
plt.title("Randomly Generated Scores")
plt.show()
            </pre>
            <p>With this project, I explored Matplotlib’s ability to quickly generate insightful graphs. By randomly assigning scores to names, I was able to practice formatting and labeling charts, which is a crucial skill in data storytelling.</p>
        </div>
